Class UMLRelationship

java.lang.Object
com.example.umlscd.Models.ClassDiagram.UMLRelationship
public class UMLRelationship extends Object

UML Relationship

The UMLRelationship class represents a UML Relationship within the UML Editor application. It encapsulates the properties of a relationship between two UML elements, such as classes or interfaces. This class is designed to be serializable, allowing for the persistence and retrieval of relationship data through JSON serialization and deserialization using the Jackson library.

Key functionalities include:

  • Storing the type of relationship (e.g., Association, Aggregation, Composition, Inheritance).
  • Maintaining references to the start and end elements involved in the relationship.
  • Capturing additional details such as the relationship name and multiplicities at both ends.
  • Providing methods to access and modify the relationship's properties.

Authors: Ahmad Wyne, Wahaj Asif, Muhammad Muneeb

Version: 1.0

Since: 2024-12-03

    • UMLRelationship

      public UMLRelationship(String type, String startElementName, String endElementName, String name, String startMultiplicity, String endMultiplicity)
      Constructs a UMLRelationship with the specified properties.

      This constructor initializes the relationship with its type, start and end element names, name, and multiplicities.

      Parameters:
      type - The type of the relationship (e.g., Association, Aggregation).
      startElementName - The name of the starting UML element in the relationship.
      endElementName - The name of the ending UML element in the relationship.
      name - The name of the relationship.
      startMultiplicity - The multiplicity at the start end of the relationship.
      endMultiplicity - The multiplicity at the end end of the relationship.
